1
00:00:00,398 --> 00:00:04,337
(The entrance through which trade and modernization entered Korea)

2
00:00:04,338 --> 00:00:08,848
(Where a city meets nature)

3
00:00:09,348 --> 00:00:12,578
(Today's destination is surrounded by romantic blue waves.)

4
00:00:13,718 --> 00:00:17,388
(Incheon Metropolitan City)

5
00:00:17,818 --> 00:00:20,758
(A wet fog covers the city this morning.)

6
00:00:21,288 --> 00:00:22,557
The ocean fog is no joke.

7
00:00:22,558 --> 00:00:24,088
- It's really foggy.
- Yes.

8
00:00:24,588 --> 00:00:25,998
- Hello.
- Hello.

9
00:00:26,328 --> 00:00:27,328
Good morning.

10
00:00:27,328 --> 00:00:28,328
- Hello.
- Hello.

11
00:00:28,329 --> 00:00:29,597
- Hello.
- Hello.

12
00:00:29,598 --> 00:00:31,128
- Nice to see you.
- It's much warmer.

13
00:00:31,328 --> 00:00:32,367
- Hello.
- I'm grateful for that.

14
00:00:32,368 --> 00:00:33,498
- It's warmer.
- Yes.

15
00:00:33,598 --> 00:00:34,668
Wolmi Island.

16
00:00:34,768 --> 00:00:36,038
Incheon's amazing.

17
00:00:36,868 --> 00:00:39,578
Now I get why so many people choose to live here.

18
00:00:39,738 --> 00:00:41,038
- Why?
- It's so nice.

19
00:00:41,638 --> 00:00:44,047
It's pretty close to Seoul.

20
00:00:44,048 --> 00:00:45,207
- Yes.
- It's great.

21
00:00:45,208 --> 00:00:46,377
It took 90 minutes.

22
00:00:46,378 --> 00:00:47,517
That's not far from Seoul.

23
00:00:47,518 --> 00:00:49,147
Im Cheol, Incheon.

24
00:00:49,148 --> 00:00:50,587
- It rhymes.
- It's nice.

25
00:00:50,588 --> 00:00:52,048
- It sounds similar.
- Yes.

26
00:00:52,158 --> 00:00:54,758
Our program's YouTube channel.

27
00:00:54,788 --> 00:00:56,127
It's newly opened.

28
00:00:56,128 --> 00:00:57,327
- It came up yesterday.
- And...

29
00:00:57,328 --> 00:00:59,328
thanks to an active social media presence,

30
00:00:59,458 --> 00:01:01,927
we're getting lots of reels showing Jong Min from previous seasons.

31
00:01:01,928 --> 00:01:02,967
- What, really?
- I thought...

32
00:01:02,968 --> 00:01:04,798
you'd been ingesting preservatives.

33
00:01:05,098 --> 00:01:07,037
You look exactly the same as you did then.

34
00:01:07,038 --> 00:01:08,678
- Really? Don't I look better now?
- Yes.

35
00:01:09,508 --> 00:01:11,067
I think you look a bit better now.

36
00:01:11,068 --> 00:01:12,407
That could be true.

37
00:01:12,408 --> 00:01:14,607
- Old clips are resurfacing.
- Back then...

38
00:01:14,608 --> 00:01:15,848
I acted pretty stupid.

39
00:01:16,248 --> 00:01:18,308
When you were sedated. That was hilarious.

40
00:01:18,948 --> 00:01:20,047
I'd never seen someone...

41
00:01:20,048 --> 00:01:21,647
who woke up during a procedure.

42
00:01:21,648 --> 00:01:23,317
- I don't remember that.
- Only 3.3 percent do that.

43
00:01:23,318 --> 00:01:25,248
- Yes.
- That really surprised me.

44
00:01:25,588 --> 00:01:28,518
(That was in 2015 when Jong Min got a full physical.)

45
00:01:29,028 --> 00:01:32,198
(He was sedated for an endoscopy.)

46
00:01:34,998 --> 00:01:39,038
(Zombie Kim beat the anesthesia meds.)

47
00:01:39,538 --> 00:01:40,538
(Yelling)

48
00:01:41,638 --> 00:01:43,338
- Today's destination is...
- Oh, right.

49
00:01:44,168 --> 00:01:45,638
Incheon Metropolitan City.

50
00:01:46,338 --> 00:01:47,908
- Inchen.
- A metropolitan city.

51
00:01:48,638 --> 00:01:51,478
And this is the Wolmi Island theme park which lots of people...

52
00:01:52,248 --> 00:01:53,678
have fond memories of.

53
00:01:54,348 --> 00:01:55,548
Lots of memories.

54
00:01:56,288 --> 00:01:57,447
I was here...

55
00:01:57,448 --> 00:01:59,057
with Se Yoon a few months ago.

56
00:01:59,058 --> 00:02:01,358
He went webfoot octopus fishing with my son and I.

57
00:02:01,488 --> 00:02:02,987
The three of us...

58
00:02:02,988 --> 00:02:04,427
- hung out here too.
- Yes.

59
00:02:04,428 --> 00:02:05,997
- He played with my son.
- Right.

60
00:02:05,998 --> 00:02:07,757
I was too scared to ride the Pirate Ship,

61
00:02:07,758 --> 00:02:08,898
so Se Yoon went instead.

62
00:02:09,398 --> 00:02:12,297
(Happy memories from that day)

63
00:02:12,298 --> 00:02:13,997
Joon, have you been here?

64
00:02:13,998 --> 00:02:15,638
- Yes, often.
- We talked on the way here

65
00:02:16,268 --> 00:02:18,907
I said, "Didn't we come here not long ago?"

66
00:02:18,908 --> 00:02:21,338
He said, "No. I came here with my girlfriend."

67
00:02:22,078 --> 00:02:23,147
- He said that.
- Come on.

68
00:02:23,148 --> 00:02:24,708
Do you think this is a YouTube channel?

69
00:02:24,808 --> 00:02:26,617
- Why would you...
- It goes on YouTube too!

70
00:02:26,618 --> 00:02:28,447
Is this a clip exclusive for YouTube?

71
00:02:28,448 --> 00:02:30,729
- It is for YouTube.
- Didn't you come here with someone?

72
00:02:30,788 --> 00:02:32,487
- With whom?
- You mentioned a woman.

73
00:02:32,488 --> 00:02:35,187
Well, I said... I came with someone I knew.

74
00:02:35,188 --> 00:02:36,988
Why is he so flustered?

75
00:02:37,758 --> 00:02:39,397
- He said that.
- There's a crowd here.

76
00:02:39,398 --> 00:02:40,428
That's hilarious.

77
00:02:40,598 --> 00:02:43,728
Actually, Eurwangni and Wolmi Island...

78
00:02:44,128 --> 00:02:45,327
It was the place to go.

79
00:02:45,328 --> 00:02:47,568
Back when I was in high school,

80
00:02:47,868 --> 00:02:50,137
it was the hottest place to hang out at.

81
00:02:50,138 --> 00:02:51,267
Especially Wolmi Island.

82
00:02:51,268 --> 00:02:52,907
It was so popular,

83
00:02:52,908 --> 00:02:54,107
- it was overcrowded.
- It was crazy.

84
00:02:54,108 --> 00:02:56,308
Wolmi... That goes for Wolmi Island too.

85
00:02:56,808 --> 00:02:58,048
Who did I come here with?

86
00:02:58,948 --> 00:03:00,717
- I can't remember, it was ages ago.
- An acquaintance.

87
00:03:00,718 --> 00:03:02,447
- It was so long ago.
- And you were here often.

88
00:03:02,448 --> 00:03:04,147
- Joon knew a lot of people.
- Yes.

89
00:03:04,148 --> 00:03:05,148
Not anymore.

90
00:03:05,149 --> 00:03:07,557
I came as a kid for the gastropods and silkworm chrysalis.

91
00:03:07,558 --> 00:03:08,617
- With Dad.
- They're still available.

92
00:03:08,618 --> 00:03:09,927
- Are they?
- They're still for sale.

93
00:03:09,928 --> 00:03:11,028
How do you know so well?

94
00:03:11,688 --> 00:03:12,857
Another acquaintance...

95
00:03:12,858 --> 00:03:13,998
(That's suspicious.)

96
00:03:14,128 --> 00:03:15,327
- Good for you.
- They're acquaintances.

97
00:03:15,328 --> 00:03:17,327
I have lots of acquaintances.

98
00:03:17,328 --> 00:03:19,167
So, again today,

99
00:03:19,168 --> 00:03:22,438
we want to help you create some amazing memories.

100
00:03:23,168 --> 00:03:25,607
The theme of the trip that will let that happen is...

101
00:03:25,608 --> 00:03:26,638
The theme.

102
00:03:26,938 --> 00:03:29,007
Lying on the Incheon Seashore.

103
00:03:29,008 --> 00:03:30,048
That's the title.

104
00:03:30,148 --> 00:03:32,518
- What's that?
- It's a song.

105
00:03:33,078 --> 00:03:34,078
(Doesn't it go like this?)

106
00:03:34,079 --> 00:03:36,687
- You try so hard each week.
- "Don't become a lonely seabird."

107
00:03:36,688 --> 00:03:37,688
I was given a script.

108
00:03:37,689 --> 00:03:39,317
"Lying on the Incheon seashore."

109
00:03:39,318 --> 00:03:40,557
(Se Yoon gives him a crash course.)

110
00:03:40,558 --> 00:03:42,058
- That's the tune.
- Sing it again.

111
00:03:42,528 --> 00:03:44,487
(Lying on the Incheon seashore)

112
00:03:44,488 --> 00:03:46,257
- "Don't become..."
- "Lying on the Incheon seashore."

113
00:03:46,258 --> 00:03:47,557
- Oh, I see.
- That's the title.

114
00:03:47,558 --> 00:03:49,567
I heard you had been taking singing lessons.

115
00:03:49,568 --> 00:03:51,628
- I see.
- You work as a group.

116
00:03:52,268 --> 00:03:53,898
Through the group missions,

117
00:03:54,268 --> 00:03:56,007
we'll figure out how many of you...

118
00:03:56,008 --> 00:03:57,237
must sleep on the seashore...

119
00:03:57,238 --> 00:03:58,407
- facing the Incheon sea.
- What?

120
00:03:58,408 --> 00:03:59,908
- We decide that already?
- Already?

121
00:04:01,108 --> 00:04:04,508
(The seaside is plunged into darkness at night.)

122
00:04:05,278 --> 00:04:06,577
It might have gotten warmer,

123
00:04:06,578 --> 00:04:08,247
- but the seaside...
- It's still cold.

124
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:09,317
(How many will sleep here?)

125
00:04:09,318 --> 00:04:10,948
Each time you fail a mission,

126
00:04:11,248 --> 00:04:13,358
the number of those sleeping outdoors will increase.

127
00:04:13,688 --> 00:04:15,728
Who will actually sleep outdoors...

128
00:04:16,058 --> 00:04:17,858
will be decided later on.

129
00:04:18,128 --> 00:04:19,197
We don't decide that?

130
00:04:19,198 --> 00:04:21,828
The fact that we decide the number means it could be zero.

131
00:04:21,998 --> 00:04:23,027
- Yes.
- Right.

132
00:04:23,028 --> 00:04:24,197
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

133
00:04:24,198 --> 00:04:26,767
- Two or three usually go outdoors.
- Yes.

134
00:04:26,768 --> 00:04:28,567
I'm thinking this could be better for us.

135
00:04:28,568 --> 00:04:29,907
But if things go wrong,

136
00:04:29,908 --> 00:04:31,807
- we could all end up outside.
- Yes.

137
00:04:31,808 --> 00:04:33,477
- That could happen.
- The worst case scenario.

138
00:04:33,478 --> 00:04:35,477
- Would that happen? We're pros.
- Right.

139
00:04:35,478 --> 00:04:37,448
No. We're at a pretty high level.

140
00:04:37,648 --> 00:04:40,217
- We are.
- We've been doing well lately.

141
00:04:40,218 --> 00:04:42,077
- We're great as a group.
- Our teamwork is awesome.

142
00:04:42,078 --> 00:04:43,147
Yes. We work well together.

143
00:04:43,148 --> 00:04:44,287
The fit one, the smart...

144
00:04:44,288 --> 00:04:45,487
- The capital city guy.
- Yes.

145
00:04:45,488 --> 00:04:46,787
I know all the capital cities.

146
00:04:46,788 --> 00:04:48,417
Brussels, Belgium. I know them all.

147
00:04:48,418 --> 00:04:49,587
(A perfect balance?)

148
00:04:49,588 --> 00:04:52,527
We'll move just a bit...

149
00:04:52,528 --> 00:04:54,457
for the first mission.

150
00:04:54,458 --> 00:04:56,367
- Okay.
- Let's get things started!

151
00:04:56,368 --> 00:04:57,427
- Let's go.
- Okay.

152
00:04:57,428 --> 00:04:58,628
- Let's go.
- Good luck, guys.

153
00:04:59,168 --> 00:05:01,198
Lying on the Incheon seashore!

154
00:05:01,668 --> 00:05:03,468
Who will end up sleeping outdoors?

155
00:05:03,868 --> 00:05:05,167
Korea's best...

156
00:05:05,168 --> 00:05:07,108
real wild road variety show!

157
00:05:07,338 --> 00:05:08,438
Who are we?

158
00:05:08,838 --> 00:05:09,878
2 Days...

159
00:05:09,948 --> 00:05:12,278
- 1 Night!
- 1 Night!

160
00:05:13,448 --> 00:05:16,918
(What kind of trip awaits them today?)

161
00:05:17,348 --> 00:05:18,448
It has been a long time.

162
00:05:18,918 --> 00:05:20,518
It's quiet today.

163
00:05:20,788 --> 00:05:22,727
It's the same as when I was in high school.

164
00:05:22,728 --> 00:05:24,327
Yes. It looks the same.

165
00:05:24,328 --> 00:05:26,228
Don't you want to play that again?

166
00:05:26,928 --> 00:05:28,727
Doesn't it feel peaceful today?

167
00:05:28,728 --> 00:05:31,128
- Yes. I hope it stays peaceful.
- It's quiet.

168
00:05:31,668 --> 00:05:33,667
Compared to last week, the weather...

169
00:05:33,668 --> 00:05:34,837
- It's great.
- It's the best.

170
00:05:34,838 --> 00:05:36,367
- Last week...
- If it's like this,

171
00:05:36,368 --> 00:05:38,038
- I wouldn't mind getting wet.
- No.

172
00:05:39,338 --> 00:05:40,538
I think I'd mind.

173
00:05:41,308 --> 00:05:43,248
I'm most afraid of the peace.

174
00:05:43,548 --> 00:05:44,678
Don't be afraid.

175
00:05:45,578 --> 00:05:46,818
Where are we going?

176
00:05:47,618 --> 00:05:49,217
This is the amusement park.

177
00:05:49,218 --> 00:05:51,564
- We're going to the amusement park.
- There's the Disco Pang Pang.

178
00:05:51,588 --> 00:05:52,948
We're going to the amusement park.

179
00:05:53,088 --> 00:05:54,457
- I love it.
- This should be fun.

180
00:05:54,458 --> 00:05:56,387
(They reach a Wolmi Island amusement park.)

181
00:05:56,388 --> 00:05:57,488
This is madness.

182
00:05:57,958 --> 00:05:59,227
I've never been on this before.

183
00:05:59,228 --> 00:06:01,097
At our age, one ride on this and you ache the next day.

184
00:06:01,098 --> 00:06:02,098
Everyone.

185
00:06:02,099 --> 00:06:03,928
We came all the way to Wolmi Island.

186
00:06:04,368 --> 00:06:06,638
You should ride something thrilling.

187
00:06:07,738 --> 00:06:08,968
That's the worst.

188
00:06:09,338 --> 00:06:10,767
(He weighs 120kg.)

189
00:06:10,768 --> 00:06:12,268
- Gosh.
- This is bad.

190
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:14,508
- I throw up.
- Do you really?

191
00:06:14,608 --> 00:06:15,807
- Oh, dear.
- I don't remember.

192
00:06:15,808 --> 00:06:18,678
The mission you'll take part in here...

193
00:06:19,378 --> 00:06:21,448
is called the Extreme Wolmi Tour.

194
00:06:21,648 --> 00:06:23,217
- That sounds fun.
- We'll feel nauseous?

195
00:06:23,218 --> 00:06:24,817
- That's scary.
- "Wolmi."

196
00:06:24,818 --> 00:06:25,858
(A nauseating tour?)

197
00:06:27,418 --> 00:06:28,557
There are three courses.

198
00:06:28,558 --> 00:06:31,757
You just have to successfully complete two.

199
00:06:31,758 --> 00:06:33,197
(They must complete two out of three.)

200
00:06:33,198 --> 00:06:34,297
If you fail,

201
00:06:34,298 --> 00:06:36,397
two people will have to sleep outdoors.

202
00:06:36,398 --> 00:06:37,697
- Already?
- Two people?

203
00:06:37,698 --> 00:06:38,867
- Yes.
- You can't allocate...

204
00:06:38,868 --> 00:06:39,997
two out of five already.

205
00:06:39,998 --> 00:06:42,037
Two people as soon as we get started...

206
00:06:42,038 --> 00:06:44,207
We could all end up sleeping outdoors.

207
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:45,407
Yes. I said so.

208
00:06:45,408 --> 00:06:46,938
We could be done by lunchtime.

209
00:06:47,138 --> 00:06:48,207
Let's give it our all.

210
00:06:48,208 --> 00:06:50,148
- The first mission.
- We can succeed.

211
00:06:50,778 --> 00:06:53,448
Take a Selfie Video on Disco Pang Pang.

212
00:06:53,478 --> 00:06:54,478
- A selfie video?
- Yes.

213
00:06:54,479 --> 00:06:56,799
- While we're on the ride?
- You'll be on Disco Pang Pang.

214
00:06:56,888 --> 00:06:59,287
Your mission is to take a selfie video...

215
00:06:59,288 --> 00:07:00,817
and your faces can't go out of frame.

216
00:07:00,818 --> 00:07:01,987
- We have to take a video?
- Yes.

217
00:07:01,988 --> 00:07:03,888
The ride will last for three minutes.

218
00:07:04,228 --> 00:07:05,287
Even if one group fails the mission,

219
00:07:05,288 --> 00:07:06,997
as long as the other group succeeds, it's considered successful.

220
00:07:06,998 --> 00:07:08,297
- Really?
- Okay.

221
00:07:08,298 --> 00:07:10,627
We'll be right here and checking the video.

222
00:07:10,628 --> 00:07:12,737
So the moment your faces go out of frame, you've failed.

223
00:07:12,738 --> 00:07:13,738
- My gosh.
- I see.

224
00:07:13,739 --> 00:07:15,297
- You've completed the mission...
- My gosh.

225
00:07:15,298 --> 00:07:16,367
If one of the group makes it.

226
00:07:16,368 --> 00:07:17,907
Who's feeling confident about this mission?

227
00:07:17,908 --> 00:07:19,007
- Are you feeling confident?
- Me. I'm feeling confident.

228
00:07:19,008 --> 00:07:20,137
Isn't it better to pair up...

229
00:07:20,138 --> 00:07:21,377
- the members who feel confident?
- Right.

230
00:07:21,378 --> 00:07:22,477
- Come here.
- Let's do this. Okay.

231
00:07:22,478 --> 00:07:25,447
Here's what we should do. Let's put our faces together...

232
00:07:25,448 --> 00:07:27,317
- and hold the camera.
- That's it. Yes.

233
00:07:27,318 --> 00:07:29,017
- That will be better.
- Yes. Let's do that.

234
00:07:29,018 --> 00:07:31,048
- Okay. Right.
- So you guys will probably fail.

235
00:07:31,188 --> 00:07:33,087
All right. Get your faces on camera now.

236
00:07:33,088 --> 00:07:34,118
Let's go.

237
00:07:34,288 --> 00:07:35,588
Make it rough.

238
00:07:36,858 --> 00:07:38,558
Hold on. You want me to hold the phone?

239
00:07:39,028 --> 00:07:40,527
Of course. You can't expect us to do it.

240
00:07:40,528 --> 00:07:41,697
(Seon Ho will hold the camera for the trio.)

241
00:07:41,698 --> 00:07:43,728
Joon. Come here. Listen.

242
00:07:43,898 --> 00:07:45,828
- I'll hold the phone like this.
- Yes.

243
00:07:46,368 --> 00:07:48,598
- You have to stay close to me.
- Okay.

244
00:07:48,898 --> 00:07:50,868
We need to hold each other close like this.

245
00:07:52,308 --> 00:07:54,678
- Are you okay with this?
- Why don't you guys just kiss?

246
00:07:54,878 --> 00:07:56,477
- I'm good.
- This should be enough.

247
00:07:56,478 --> 00:07:57,978
Hey. This is nothing. Come on.

248
00:07:58,578 --> 00:08:00,477
If we can't even do this...

249
00:08:00,478 --> 00:08:02,787
You need to watch our faces and adjust the phone.

250
00:08:02,788 --> 00:08:03,848
I'm going to throw up.

251
00:08:03,948 --> 00:08:04,948
- You have to...
- Look at the camera.

252
00:08:04,949 --> 00:08:06,829
It will be a jumpy ride. What will you do then?

253
00:08:07,218 --> 00:08:08,458
- This is better. Right?
- Yes.

254
00:08:08,718 --> 00:08:10,227
- You...
- You have to hold your arm still.

255
00:08:10,228 --> 00:08:11,557
- You know what I mean, right?
- This is better, right?

256
00:08:11,558 --> 00:08:12,658
- Yes.
- Like this.

