00:16:44,879 --> 00:16:46,178
(to assemble the letters.)

512
00:16:46,179 --> 00:16:49,448
(He can't open his eyes.)

513
00:16:49,449 --> 00:16:50,449
(Screaming)

514
00:16:51,619 --> 00:16:52,689
Open your eyes!

515
00:16:53,759 --> 00:16:56,429
(But he can't.)

516
00:16:57,589 --> 00:16:59,698
- I'm going to kill him.
- I can't do it.

517
00:16:59,699 --> 00:17:01,328
Open your eyes. Why won't you open them?

518
00:17:01,329 --> 00:17:02,829
His scarf is hitting his face.

519
00:17:06,269 --> 00:17:07,638
(Glaring)

520
00:17:07,639 --> 00:17:09,408
They forced me to ride this.

521
00:17:09,409 --> 00:17:11,238
- This is crazy.
- I can't do it.

522
00:17:11,239 --> 00:17:12,739
- Stop it.
- I can't do it.

523
00:17:13,109 --> 00:17:15,239
- I can't do it!
- Stop it!

524
00:17:19,179 --> 00:17:21,218
(Z, A, E, J, M, O, I, L, G, P, T, W, P, A, N, S)

525
00:17:21,219 --> 00:17:23,319
(Did he take a good look at the letters?)

526
00:17:23,619 --> 00:17:26,319
(This is their last chance to look at the letters.)

527
00:17:26,719 --> 00:17:28,459
This is so scary.

528
00:17:28,819 --> 00:17:30,259
Gosh, it's going up too high.

529
00:17:30,459 --> 00:17:32,428
Open your eyes. Their eyes are closed.

530
00:17:32,429 --> 00:17:34,799
(Was Seon Ho able to see the letters?)

531
00:17:35,159 --> 00:17:38,228
(The slingshot finally comes to a stop.)

532
00:17:38,229 --> 00:17:39,968
- That's hard.
- Shin Saimdang. What's that?

533
00:17:39,969 --> 00:17:41,515
(Retrieving the board, not allowing them to take a peek)

534
00:17:41,539 --> 00:17:43,708
(Trying to assemble the letters in his head)

535
00:17:43,709 --> 00:17:45,168
- Please.
- I can't.

536
00:17:45,169 --> 00:17:46,908
This is killing me.

537
00:17:46,909 --> 00:17:48,478
(All he did was get scared.)

538
00:17:48,479 --> 00:17:49,678
Getting on the ride isn't everything.

539
00:17:49,679 --> 00:17:51,479
He couldn't keep his eyes open.

540
00:17:52,049 --> 00:17:53,978
(They come down.)

541
00:17:53,979 --> 00:17:55,019
I can't do this.

542
00:17:55,319 --> 00:17:56,519
Where are the letters?

543
00:17:57,119 --> 00:17:58,188
- Are you okay?
- Jong Min.

544
00:17:58,189 --> 00:17:59,458
I couldn't even see one letter.

545
00:17:59,459 --> 00:18:00,518
(Laughing)

546
00:18:00,519 --> 00:18:02,188
(I couldn't even see one letter.)

547
00:18:02,189 --> 00:18:03,189
Try to guess it, though.

548
00:18:03,190 --> 00:18:04,688
- Guess it.
- Is it going to go up again?

549
00:18:04,689 --> 00:18:05,959
Okay. I saw them.

550
00:18:06,359 --> 00:18:07,399
What is it?

551
00:18:07,929 --> 00:18:08,998
The first one is "Zootopia."

552
00:18:08,999 --> 00:18:10,228
- Yes.
- Okay.

553
00:18:10,229 --> 00:18:11,549
You need to guess two more right.

554
00:18:11,829 --> 00:18:14,338
- Make it happen.
- There are three titles.

555
00:18:14,339 --> 00:18:15,738
- "Zootopia."
- Okay.

556
00:18:15,739 --> 00:18:17,009
- "Nameless Gangster."
- Okay.

557
00:18:20,239 --> 00:18:22,339
- What else?
- You can do this.

558
00:18:23,009 --> 00:18:24,979
- Me...
- You didn't see anything?

559
00:18:25,249 --> 00:18:26,848
I only saw "Z."

560
00:18:26,849 --> 00:18:28,878
"Zootopia," "Nameless Gangster," and...

561
00:18:28,879 --> 00:18:30,349
(Please get it right.)

562
00:18:31,719 --> 00:18:33,388
- "Tazza."
- Wrong.

563
00:18:33,389 --> 00:18:34,818
(Wrong answer)

564
00:18:34,819 --> 00:18:36,628
- My gosh.
- That was impressive, though.

565
00:18:36,629 --> 00:18:37,758
When did you open your eyes?

566
00:18:37,759 --> 00:18:39,028
- We didn't see that on camera.
- Gosh, my heart is still beating.

567
00:18:39,029 --> 00:18:40,629
I took a peek and saw the letters then.

568
00:18:40,829 --> 00:18:42,899
- Was it scary?
- Didn't we spin in the air?

569
00:18:43,329 --> 00:18:45,329
You did. But that's not important.

570
00:18:46,399 --> 00:18:47,668
I'm not okay at all.

571
00:18:47,669 --> 00:18:48,839
(Teary-eyed)

572
00:18:48,939 --> 00:18:50,769
- Here's what's important.
- Can you...

573
00:18:51,409 --> 00:18:53,129
The pain from the ride lasts only a moment.

574
00:18:53,479 --> 00:18:55,078
If we fail, we'll have to sleep outside.

575
00:18:55,079 --> 00:18:56,708
I'd rather sleep outside.

576
00:18:56,709 --> 00:18:57,709
- Hey.
- Really?

577
00:18:57,710 --> 00:19:00,349
Do you know why people make mistakes?

578
00:19:00,449 --> 00:19:01,929
They can't be patient at that moment.

579
00:19:02,179 --> 00:19:04,289
- Really?
- That's the biggest downfall.

580
00:19:04,449 --> 00:19:05,749
So people make mistakes.

581
00:19:06,019 --> 00:19:07,888
Come here, Seon Ho.

582
00:19:07,889 --> 00:19:08,889
- I must act in my new project.
- All right.

583
00:19:08,890 --> 00:19:10,329
- Joon, go to the left.
- Why?

584
00:19:10,689 --> 00:19:11,858
- I can't do it.
- There.

585
00:19:11,859 --> 00:19:14,258
We'll give you a chance to redeem yourself from the previous one.

586
00:19:14,259 --> 00:19:15,558
Redeem myself from what? I did a good job earlier.

587
00:19:15,559 --> 00:19:16,628
Let's complete the mission.

588
00:19:16,629 --> 00:19:17,828
Do you want to give it a try?

589
00:19:17,829 --> 00:19:18,829
- Okay. Let's do this.
- Let's do it.

590
00:19:18,830 --> 00:19:20,869
How high does it go up to?

591
00:19:21,369 --> 00:19:22,668
- How many meters?
- Wait.

592
00:19:22,669 --> 00:19:24,139
Let me check if my bottom fits.

593
00:19:24,709 --> 00:19:26,009
Let me check if my bottom fits.

594
00:19:26,409 --> 00:19:28,939
(Se Yoon felt bad for pushing Joon to get on the ride.)

595
00:19:29,779 --> 00:19:30,779
It's so tight.

596
00:19:30,780 --> 00:19:32,125
(He voluntarily gets on the ride.)

597
00:19:32,149 --> 00:19:33,648
What? Se Yoon will ride it?

598
00:19:33,649 --> 00:19:34,979
Hey, Se Yoon will ride it!

599
00:19:35,219 --> 00:19:36,818
(Deeply moved)

600
00:19:36,819 --> 00:19:38,389
Se Yoon is going to do it!

601
00:19:39,519 --> 00:19:40,519
It's too tight. No!

602
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:41,588
- You can't ride it.
- He's going to ride it?

603
00:19:41,589 --> 00:19:43,389
Really? Are you sure?

604
00:19:43,729 --> 00:19:44,758
I must get off.

605
00:19:44,759 --> 00:19:46,598
(He can't ride it as he's too fat.)

606
00:19:46,599 --> 00:19:48,119
- I can't ride it!
- He can't ride it.

607
00:19:48,459 --> 00:19:49,729
Sir, unfasten it, please.

608
00:19:49,929 --> 00:19:51,299
He can't ride it? Come on.

609
00:19:51,429 --> 00:19:52,599
Hey, I'll ride it.

610
00:19:52,669 --> 00:19:53,838
But he said I couldn't.

611
00:19:53,839 --> 00:19:55,098
(He gets to boast without getting on the ride.)

612
00:19:55,099 --> 00:19:57,068
It must go all the way down how it did for DinDin.

613
00:19:57,069 --> 00:19:58,239
But it didn't for me.

614
00:19:58,639 --> 00:20:00,878
Will it go up slowly and come down?

615
00:20:00,879 --> 00:20:02,539
No. It will shoot up in one go.

616
00:20:02,809 --> 00:20:03,879
Wait!

617
00:20:04,649 --> 00:20:06,078
Hold on.

618
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:07,979
(Relieved)

619
00:20:08,449 --> 00:20:09,888
Joon, any last words?

620
00:20:09,889 --> 00:20:12,119
I'm sorry. Nothing comes to mind.

621
00:20:12,189 --> 00:20:13,819
What about you? Aren't you scared?

622
00:20:14,259 --> 00:20:15,919
I don't know yet.

623
00:20:16,089 --> 00:20:17,728
- All right.
- Wait.

624
00:20:17,729 --> 00:20:19,129
(The bulky guy gets scared easily.)

625
00:20:19,459 --> 00:20:21,859
Why... Darn it. This is so annoying.

626
00:20:22,599 --> 00:20:24,269
DinDin, hold onto your front teeth.

627
00:20:24,599 --> 00:20:26,569
- Wait.
- I hate it!

628
00:20:27,099 --> 00:20:29,268
- Gosh, Joon.
- How long does it last?

629
00:20:29,269 --> 00:20:30,308
Are you okay, Joon?

630
00:20:30,309 --> 00:20:31,708
(Shaking in fear)

631
00:20:31,709 --> 00:20:32,839
Are you okay, DinDin?

632
00:20:33,379 --> 00:20:35,738
My gosh. That must be so scary.

633
00:20:35,739 --> 00:20:37,678
- Please, DinDin.
- Complete the mission!

634
00:20:37,679 --> 00:20:39,078
- DinDin.
- You're ready, right?

635
00:20:39,079 --> 00:20:41,579
The category of the keywords is four-character idioms.

636
00:20:41,719 --> 00:20:43,418
- Four-character idioms.
- There are four idioms.

637
00:20:43,419 --> 00:20:44,588
- Four.
- Four idioms?

638
00:20:44,589 --> 00:20:45,818
- Yes.
- There are four.

639
00:20:45,819 --> 00:20:48,219
- So it's 4 times 4.
- You need to assemble the idioms.

640
00:20:49,729 --> 00:20:51,588
- This is killing me.
- Here we go!

641
00:20:51,589 --> 00:20:52,589
Joon.

642
00:20:52,590 --> 00:20:55,659
Three, two, one.

643
00:20:56,829 --> 00:20:57,829
Go!

644
00:20:57,830 --> 00:21:01,838
(Shooting up)

645
00:21:01,839 --> 00:21:02,839
Go!

646
00:21:02,839 --> 00:21:03,839
(Screaming)

647
00:21:05,109 --> 00:21:07,979
(The two of them didn't close their eyes for now.)

648
00:21:09,809 --> 00:21:12,308
(Will they be able to clearly see the letters?)

649
00:21:12,309 --> 00:21:13,455
- My gosh.
- That's way too high.

650
00:21:13,479 --> 00:21:15,848
(I rode that?)

651
00:21:15,849 --> 00:21:17,189
- My gosh.
- That's way too high.

652
00:21:17,589 --> 00:21:19,818
- Wait. Assemble the idioms.
- No way.

653
00:21:19,819 --> 00:21:20,958
(Revealing the letters)

654
00:21:20,959 --> 00:21:25,128
(DinDin's camera)

655
00:21:25,129 --> 00:21:29,499
(DinDin's camera)

656
00:21:31,269 --> 00:21:32,299
I saw, "long."

657
00:21:32,939 --> 00:21:35,568
- Longing for it day and night.
- Longing for it day and night.

658
00:21:35,569 --> 00:21:36,668
- And...
- Longing for it day and night.

659
00:21:36,669 --> 00:21:40,138
(He assembled "longing for it day and night?")

660
00:21:40,139 --> 00:21:41,508
- Longing for it day and night.
- Longing for it day and night.

661
00:21:41,509 --> 00:21:42,538
- A blessing in disguise.
- A blessing...

662
00:21:42,539 --> 00:21:43,608
- in disguise.
- Longing for it day and night.

663
00:21:43,609 --> 00:21:44,678
A blessing in disguise.

664
00:21:44,679 --> 00:21:47,419
(Joon assembles "a blessing in disguise" too.)

665
00:21:47,779 --> 00:21:51,089
(The slingshot is shaking even more.)

666
00:21:51,989 --> 00:21:54,319
Hey, look at Joon.

667
00:21:54,459 --> 00:21:56,135
It's not spinning around. Turn around now!

668
00:21:56,159 --> 00:21:57,459
Longing for it day and night.

669
00:21:57,659 --> 00:21:59,999
A blessing in disguise.

670
00:22:00,359 --> 00:22:01,898
- You...
- Longing for it day and night.

671
00:22:01,899 --> 00:22:03,075
- A blessing in disguise.
- You...

672
00:22:03,099 --> 00:22:05,168
(DinDin spots "you.")

673
00:22:05,169 --> 00:22:06,598
- You reap what you sow.
- You reap what you sow.

674
00:22:06,599 --> 00:22:08,175
- You reap what you sow.
- What's the other one?

675
00:22:08,199 --> 00:22:10,968
(They only have one idiom left to go.)

676
00:22:10,969 --> 00:22:12,238
Let's remove it.

677
00:22:12,239 --> 00:22:13,239
(Retrieving the board, not allowing them to take a peek)

678
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:14,738
- Why?
- Why?

679
00:22:14,739 --> 00:22:16,138
- Why are you taking it away?
- No.

680
00:22:16,139 --> 00:22:17,555
- Why are you taking it away?
- It's over now.

681
00:22:17,579 --> 00:22:19,779
- Why are you taking it away?
- They must get it right.

682
00:22:20,019 --> 00:22:21,678
- It's not turning around.
- I can't see anything.

683
00:22:21,679 --> 00:22:22,778
(Were they able to see the last one?)

684
00:22:22,779 --> 00:22:23,788
Hey, did you see them?

685
00:22:23,789 --> 00:22:25,795
Did you assemble them? Or do you want to go again now?

686
00:22:25,819 --> 00:22:27,889
All right. Tell me the answers.

687
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:30,049
Longing for it day and night.

688
00:22:31,159 --> 00:22:32,229
A blessing in disguise.

689
00:22:35,199 --> 00:22:37,898
(Longing for it day and night, a blessing in disguise)

690
00:22:37,899 --> 00:22:39,368
(The remaining idioms are...)

691
00:22:39,369 --> 00:22:41,129
(you reap what you sow and no pain no gain.)

692
00:22:42,069 --> 00:22:44,169
- You reap what you sow.
- Guess one more idiom.

693
00:22:44,839 --> 00:22:46,608
Just guess one. We couldn't see it either.

694
00:22:46,609 --> 00:22:47,639
Follow your gut.

695
00:22:47,809 --> 00:22:50,249
(Were they able to assemble no pain no gain?)

696
00:22:51,009 --> 00:22:52,948
- No pain no gain.
- I think he's right.

697
00:22:52,949 --> 00:22:54,478
I saw "gain." It's no pain no gain.

698
00:22:54,479 --> 00:22:55,519
I think they're right.

699
00:22:56,049 --> 00:22:57,218
He froze. Joo Jong Hyun!

700
00:22:57,219 --> 00:22:58,689
- Please!
- Yes?

701
00:22:59,249 --> 00:23:01,119
- Correct.
- Okay!

702
00:23:02,189 --> 00:23:03,729
- Okay.
- Okay.

703
00:23:04,259 --> 00:23:06,128
I told you.

704
00:23:06,129 --> 00:23:07,458
- Hey, it wasn't that scary.
- Hey.

705
00:23:07,459 --> 00:23:09,899
- I'm good at everything but hiking.
- This wasn't scary.

706
00:23:10,169 --> 00:23:12,668
So you've successfully completed the second course.

707
00:23:12,669 --> 00:23:14,399
- Okay.
- All right.

708
00:23:14,839 --> 00:23:16,768
Let's go to the third course, which will be your final spot.

709
00:23:16,769 --> 00:23:18,508
- Okay!
- Okay!

710
00:23:18,509 --> 00:23:20,385
- I wanted to ride it. But I can't?
- All right.

711
00:23:20,409 --> 00:23:21,578
- Go on.
- I'm serious.

712
00:23:21,579 --> 00:23:22,809
Just get on it already.

713
00:23:22,939 --> 00:23:24,608
Don't try to sneak away. Get on the ride.

714
00:23:24,609 --> 00:23:26,008
- Right. You should ride it.
- Get on the ride.

715
00:23:26,009 --> 00:23:27,548
And you can pick one more person to join you.

716
00:23:27,549 --> 00:23:28,618
- No.
- Sir.

717
00:23:28,619 --> 00:23:30,148
Can he ride it without the safety seatbelt on?

718
00:23:30,149 --> 00:23:31,589
Can he ride it alone?

719
00:23:31,889 --> 00:23:33,488
- We're running short on time.
- Okay.

720
00:23:33,489 --> 00:23:34,518
- The cameramen...
- What are you talking about?

721
00:23:34,519 --> 00:23:36,529
Can leaves first and get a head start then.

722
00:23:36,789 --> 00:23:37,959
Get on it already.

723
00:23:38,289 --> 00:23:40,259
I'll do it if one of you joins me.

724
00:23:40,459 --> 00:23:43,069
(In the end, he gets on the slingshot.)

725
00:23:43,399 --> 00:23:45,429
(Shooting up right away)

726
00:23:45,729 --> 00:23:46,768
(Laughing)

727
00:23:46,769 --> 00:23:50,169
(In the best mood)

728
00:23:50,639 --> 00:23:54,039
(Thanks to him, they're smiling brightly this morning.)

729
00:23:57,079 --> 00:23:58,708
I'm so exhausted after that ride.

730
00:23:58,709 --> 00:24:00,218
I'm happy that DinDin and Joon did a good job.

731
00:24:00,219 --> 00:24:02,018
Right. My gosh. What a relief.

732
00:24:02,019 --> 00:24:03,749
I envy you. You got to ride it for free.

733
00:24:03,919 --> 00:24:05,088
(He doesn't mean it at all.)

734
00:24:05,089 --> 00:24:07,759
Gosh, I don't get to enjoy anything fun on this show.

735
00:24:09,219 --> 00:24:10,258
- Jong Min.
- Yes.

736
00:24:10,259 --> 00:24:11,965
- That was pretty cool of you.
- Thank you.

737
00:24:11,989 --> 00:24:13,599
I can't believe Jong Min got on it.

738
00:24:14,259 --> 00:24:16,158
I took a video with your phone.

739
00:24:16,159 --> 00:24:17,429
- Really?
- Of you on the ride.

740
00:24:17,769 --> 00:24:19,528
- It's a punch machine.
- I can't do it.

741
00:24:19,529 --> 00:24:21,368
- It's simple. Right?
- This is nice.

742
00:24:21,369 --> 00:24:22,468
Whac-A-Mole?

743
00:24:22,469 --> 00:24:23,915
- Thank you.
- Is it the punch game? What is it?

744
00:24:23,939 --> 00:24:25,409
Your final course is...

745
00:24:26,369 --> 00:24:27,378
What is it?

746
00:24:27,379 --> 00:24:28,979
Set a New Punch Machine Record.

747
00:24:29,339 --> 00:24:31,408
- It's all in the wrists.
- The record is 879 points.

748
00:24:31,409 --> 00:24:32,578
- Whose record is it?
- Whose record is it?

749
00:24:32,579 --> 00:24:33,879
It's our cameraman's.

750
00:24:34,219 --> 00:24:35,348
- Really?
- Yes.

751
00:24:35,349 --> 00:24:37,425
Once you break his record, you've completed your mission.

752
00:24:37,449 --> 00:24:38,948
You only get to try it once.

753
00:24:38,949 --> 00:24:39,988
- What?
- Only one of us?

754
00:24:39,989 --> 00:24:41,059
- Just one of us?
- Yes.

755
00:24:41,219 --> 00:24:43,158
- Come on. That doesn't sound right.
- No way. You can't do that.

756
00:24:43,159 --> 00:24:44,658
You must let us try it at least twice.

757
00:24:44,659 --> 00:24:46,528
Decide who's going to play.

758
00:24:46,529 --> 00:24:48,128
- Of course, it must be Se Yoon.
- But...

759
00:24:48,129 --> 00:24:49,129
- It has to be Se Yoon.
- Se Yoon.

760
00:24:49,130 --> 00:24:50,498
