It looks delicious.

1758
00:56:14,531 --> 00:56:16,270
(Just looking at the meat makes him smile.)

1759
00:56:16,271 --> 00:56:17,870
You can start eating, I'll grill the meat for you.

1760
00:56:17,871 --> 00:56:18,970
- Thank you.
- Okay.

1761
00:56:18,971 --> 00:56:20,971
(Thin-sliced pork belly being placed on the grill)

1762
00:56:21,241 --> 00:56:22,871
No, let me do it. You all eat.

1763
00:56:23,711 --> 00:56:24,911
I'll just put it all here.

1764
00:56:25,011 --> 00:56:26,911
Let's grill it all.

1765
00:56:27,111 --> 00:56:29,880
(Grilling everything at once)

1766
00:56:29,881 --> 00:56:31,481
Goodness, look at this. You have it all.

1767
00:56:31,681 --> 00:56:32,720
We should eat like this.

1768
00:56:32,721 --> 00:56:34,361
(I don't think the meat will get cooked.)

1769
00:56:34,791 --> 00:56:35,890
Just unroll the slice.

1770
00:56:35,891 --> 00:56:37,097
(Meanwhile, on DinDin's table...)

1771
00:56:37,121 --> 00:56:39,561
(Unrolling each slice of meat and grilling it one by one)

1772
00:56:39,721 --> 00:56:40,920
Should I turn up the heat?

1773
00:56:40,921 --> 00:56:42,731
(How long will this take to grill?)

1774
00:56:42,861 --> 00:56:45,131
- We have to grill all at once.
- All at once?

1775
00:56:45,261 --> 00:56:46,960
- Yes, we grill everything together.
- How?

1776
00:56:46,961 --> 00:56:48,630
We put the whole thing at once to grill.

1777
00:56:48,631 --> 00:56:51,100
So you just roll and grill it?

1778
00:56:51,101 --> 00:56:52,170
- Yes.
- I'm sorry.

1779
00:56:52,171 --> 00:56:53,501
We can't have empty spots.

1780
00:56:53,901 --> 00:56:55,511
- No empty spots?
- No.

1781
00:56:56,471 --> 00:56:58,140
- Let's eat.
- Thank you for your hard work.

1782
00:56:58,141 --> 00:56:59,340
Let's eat.

1783
00:56:59,341 --> 00:57:01,111
Enjoy your meal.

1784
00:57:01,181 --> 00:57:02,251
All right.

1785
00:57:02,611 --> 00:57:04,180
Let's do this.

1786
00:57:04,181 --> 00:57:05,420
(Let's enjoy the meal.)

1787
00:57:05,421 --> 00:57:07,720
- Legendary...
- Take it all you want.

1788
00:57:07,721 --> 00:57:08,791
Legendary.

1789
00:57:09,051 --> 00:57:11,891
(Taking a bite of the meat)

1790
00:57:13,321 --> 00:57:14,660
(Another big bite of the rice)

1791
00:57:14,661 --> 00:57:15,861
Enjoy the meat.

1792
00:57:16,661 --> 00:57:19,501
(This tastes so good.)

1793
00:57:19,831 --> 00:57:24,701
(Crispy, juicy, savory flavor that bursts the moment it hits the mouth)

1794
00:57:24,741 --> 00:57:28,410
(Se Yoon, starved from wrestling, takes a big bite as well.)

1795
00:57:28,411 --> 00:57:29,471
This tastes even better.

1796
00:57:29,711 --> 00:57:31,911
Our meat is not grilled yet, how come theirs is cooked?

1797
00:57:32,311 --> 00:57:33,440
The meat isn't cooked, is it?

1798
00:57:33,441 --> 00:57:35,451
Do you want a tip?

1799
00:57:35,551 --> 00:57:37,271
We left the gas on the moment we walked in.

1800
00:57:38,321 --> 00:57:39,751
We have to be the best eaters.

1801
00:57:39,821 --> 00:57:41,320
Let's leave the gas on.

1802
00:57:41,321 --> 00:57:42,467
(Team Se Yoon left the gas on the moment they walked in.)

1803
00:57:42,491 --> 00:57:43,491
(Next-level foodie skills from the very first move)

1804
00:57:43,492 --> 00:57:44,721
They are different.

1805
00:57:45,961 --> 00:57:52,161
(The tables next to them start eating too.)

1806
00:57:52,401 --> 00:57:54,531
(Jong Min's table...)

1807
00:57:54,671 --> 00:57:57,971
(The meat is still not cooked.)

1808
00:57:58,041 --> 00:57:59,240
(Everyone else started eating.)

1809
00:57:59,241 --> 00:58:01,341
It's almost like stir-fried spicy pork, isn't it?

1810
00:58:02,241 --> 00:58:05,311
(When can we start eating?)

1811
00:58:06,211 --> 00:58:07,441
Your meat is cooked already?

1812
00:58:08,081 --> 00:58:11,081
They put only a small amount of the meat on the grill.

1813
00:58:11,211 --> 00:58:12,420
You put everything at once.

1814
00:58:12,421 --> 00:58:13,750
(You put all the meat at once.)

1815
00:58:13,751 --> 00:58:16,351
I was too greedy. I shouldn't have done that.

1816
00:58:16,891 --> 00:58:17,920
I was too greedy.

1817
00:58:17,921 --> 00:58:19,767
(The true grownup sharing life lessons through grilling meat)

1818
00:58:19,791 --> 00:58:21,467
So your dreams are becoming the ssireum champions?

1819
00:58:21,491 --> 00:58:23,830
- Yes.
- Really?

1820
00:58:23,831 --> 00:58:25,030
I want to become a celebrity.

1821
00:58:25,031 --> 00:58:27,177
- You want to become a celebrity?
- A champion and a celebrity.

1822
00:58:27,201 --> 00:58:29,500
You want to become a champion? You can surely become one.

1823
00:58:29,501 --> 00:58:30,801
You can definitely do that.

1824
00:58:31,271 --> 00:58:34,270
Ho Dong used to do wrestling. He was the champion.

1825
00:58:34,271 --> 00:58:35,671
- You know Ho Dong, right?
- Yes.

1826
00:58:35,741 --> 00:58:36,941
He was the champion.

1827
00:58:37,371 --> 00:58:39,287
Then he joined the entertainment business when he was 20.

1828
00:58:39,311 --> 00:58:40,640
That's how he started his life as a celebrity.

1829
00:58:40,641 --> 00:58:43,361
(From a top ssireum champion to a beloved TV personality nationwide)

1830
00:58:45,551 --> 00:58:47,871
He also won many Grand Awards at the Entertainment Awards.

1831
00:58:48,121 --> 00:58:50,950
Would you become a singer if you were born again?

1832
00:58:50,951 --> 00:58:52,961
- No, I would do something else.
- What?

1833
00:58:53,261 --> 00:58:55,130
A comedian?

1834
00:58:55,131 --> 00:58:57,191
No, not a celebrity.

1835
00:58:57,291 --> 00:58:58,560
You have a comedian's vibe.

1836
00:58:58,561 --> 00:58:59,561
A businessman.

1837
00:59:01,001 --> 00:59:02,001
What kind of business?

1838
00:59:02,171 --> 00:59:03,831
Something in the finance...

1839
00:59:05,441 --> 00:59:06,901
- Using your brain?
- Yes.

1840
00:59:07,041 --> 00:59:08,911
But you are a fool.

1841
00:59:10,641 --> 00:59:12,581
You act like a fool on TV.

1842
00:59:12,681 --> 00:59:13,711
That's right.

1843
00:59:14,181 --> 00:59:15,381
I'm a good actor, right?

1844
00:59:15,811 --> 00:59:17,171
You don't look like you're acting.

1845
00:59:18,381 --> 00:59:19,781
You should eat.

1846
00:59:20,121 --> 00:59:22,190
- Thank you for this.
- Enjoy, it's all cooked.

1847
00:59:22,191 --> 00:59:23,620
(Jong Min's dream of becoming a finance specialist ends here.)

1848
00:59:23,621 --> 00:59:25,420
The first question...

1849
00:59:25,421 --> 00:59:27,291
for Meat Scholarship Quiz is here.

1850
00:59:27,461 --> 00:59:29,091
I'm the smartest one on the show.

1851
00:59:29,661 --> 00:59:30,990
I'm the smartest one here.

1852
00:59:30,991 --> 00:59:32,001
(Trust me, guys.)

1853
00:59:32,101 --> 00:59:34,060
We will win no matter what...

1854
00:59:34,061 --> 00:59:35,471
if it's a general quiz.

1855
00:59:35,571 --> 00:59:36,700
- You think our table will win?
- Yes.

1856
00:59:36,701 --> 00:59:37,830
- You are elites?
- Right.

1857
00:59:37,831 --> 00:59:39,700
Really? You are the smartest ones?

1858
00:59:39,701 --> 00:59:40,771
Yes.

1859
00:59:41,271 --> 00:59:42,471
This is the first question.

1860
00:59:42,941 --> 00:59:44,540
It's related to ssireum.

1861
00:59:44,541 --> 00:59:46,701
- Okay, we have to get this.
- You can do this, right?

1862
00:59:46,781 --> 00:59:49,850
The students can't tell the answer to the show's members.

1863
00:59:49,851 --> 00:59:51,380
But Se Yoon used to be a wrestler before.

1864
00:59:51,381 --> 00:59:53,180
This quiz is just for the members.

1865
00:59:53,181 --> 00:59:54,680
This is too easy for Se Yoon.

1866
00:59:54,681 --> 00:59:55,950
It's just my image, I don't know much.

1867
00:59:55,951 --> 00:59:57,091
He used to be a wrestler.

1868
00:59:57,521 --> 00:59:59,120
- Show me.
- All right.

1869
00:59:59,121 --> 01:00:00,621
- I'll do my best.
- Okay.

1870
01:00:00,791 --> 01:00:05,000
Korea's wrestling has five classes named after...

1871
01:00:05,001 --> 01:00:06,801
Korea's mountains.

1872
01:00:07,031 --> 01:00:08,530
(This is the question.)

1873
01:00:08,531 --> 01:00:10,101
In 2024,

1874
01:00:10,631 --> 01:00:13,900
for the 1st time in 41 years since Korean ssireum was established,

1875
01:00:13,901 --> 01:00:16,971
the lightest weight class in history has been newly established.

1876
01:00:17,171 --> 01:00:18,211
Lightest weight class?

1877
01:00:18,411 --> 01:00:20,640
This class requires the athletes to be under 72kg.

1878
01:00:20,641 --> 01:00:22,610
What's the name of this class?

1879
01:00:22,611 --> 01:00:23,910
- Seon Ho.
- This one's easy.

1880
01:00:23,911 --> 01:00:24,980
This is...

1881
01:00:24,981 --> 01:00:26,020
Seon Ho.

1882
01:00:26,021 --> 01:00:27,081
Baekdu.

1883
01:00:27,381 --> 01:00:28,550
Incorrect.

1884
01:00:28,551 --> 01:00:29,551
Baekdu.

1885
01:00:29,552 --> 01:00:31,190
(Sighing)

1886
01:00:31,191 --> 01:00:32,320
That's the exact opposite.

1887
01:00:32,321 --> 01:00:33,620
(That's the exact opposite.)

1888
01:00:33,621 --> 01:00:34,621
Geumgang?

1889
01:00:35,491 --> 01:00:37,331
(It's lower than that.)

1890
01:00:37,691 --> 01:00:38,800
Halla.

1891
01:00:38,801 --> 01:00:40,000
That's too high.

1892
01:00:40,001 --> 01:00:41,570
- It has to be lower.
- Halla.

1893
01:00:41,571 --> 01:00:42,770
(Frustrated)

1894
01:00:42,771 --> 01:00:44,940
- It must be lower than Halla.
- Right.

1895
01:00:44,941 --> 01:00:46,001
It's very low.

1896
01:00:46,801 --> 01:00:47,841
(Frustrated)

1897
01:00:48,101 --> 01:00:50,311
(The lowest mountain?)

1898
01:00:51,411 --> 01:00:53,181
Se Yoon, I got the answer.

1899
01:00:53,741 --> 01:00:54,950
(He got it.)

1900
01:00:54,951 --> 01:00:56,011
Yes.

1901
01:00:56,411 --> 01:00:57,611
There is Taebaek.

1902
01:00:57,911 --> 01:00:58,921
So...

1903
01:00:59,481 --> 01:01:00,580
It must be Sobaek.

1904
01:01:00,581 --> 01:01:01,950
(Team Se Yoon: Sobaek)

1905
01:01:01,951 --> 01:01:03,290
They told him the answer.

1906
01:01:03,291 --> 01:01:05,490
Honestly, they told me the answer.

1907
01:01:05,491 --> 01:01:06,491
But I didn't go for it.

1908
01:01:06,492 --> 01:01:08,120
It's Sobaek.

1909
01:01:08,121 --> 01:01:10,160
The kids told me the answer. But I didn't go for it.

1910
01:01:10,161 --> 01:01:11,561
Se Yoon, your answer is correct.

1911
01:01:11,761 --> 01:01:12,900
- Yes!
- They told him the answer.

1912
01:01:12,901 --> 01:01:14,221
(The answer, Sobaek, is correct.)

1913
01:01:14,731 --> 01:01:16,730
(Clapping while eating)

1914
01:01:16,731 --> 01:01:17,731
You guys...

1915
01:01:17,732 --> 01:01:19,647
Why didn't you tell me the answer? So I could get it faster.

1916
01:01:19,671 --> 01:01:21,241
They didn't tell me the answer at all.

1917
01:01:21,511 --> 01:01:24,040
(That was a close one.)

1918
01:01:24,041 --> 01:01:25,180
Let's eat.

1919
01:01:25,181 --> 01:01:28,211
(Pro Ssireum Weight Class: Sobaek under 72kg)

1920
01:01:28,311 --> 01:01:31,921
(You can become the champion if you win all the weight classes.)

1921
01:01:32,121 --> 01:01:33,180
(Team Se Yoon gets meat refilled.)

1922
01:01:33,181 --> 01:01:35,197
We have to get the answer again after five minutes.

1923
01:01:35,221 --> 01:01:36,491
We are still hungry, right?

1924
01:01:37,091 --> 01:01:38,421
Let's fill our stomachs.

1925
01:01:38,691 --> 01:01:39,790
In the middle.

1926
01:01:39,791 --> 01:01:45,031
(Team Se Yoon starts to pick up the pace.)

1927
01:01:45,401 --> 01:01:47,430
(The other teams, who didn't get the answers, start eating too.)

1928
01:01:47,431 --> 01:01:49,247
- How many was that?
- So you've been doing this?

1929
01:01:49,271 --> 01:01:50,301
Let's get it.

1930
01:01:52,641 --> 01:01:54,401
You should have 3 to 4 pieces at a time.

1931
01:01:54,871 --> 01:01:55,911
Eat it all.

1932
01:01:56,311 --> 01:01:58,171
(Eating 4 pieces at a time)

1933
01:01:58,441 --> 01:02:01,211
(Eating it at the same time)

1934
01:02:01,751 --> 01:02:05,080
(The meat is vanishing at an insane speed.)

1935
01:02:05,081 --> 01:02:06,881
- We're almost done.
- We are done.

1936
01:02:07,451 --> 01:02:09,621
We're almost done. I just had two pieces.

1937
01:02:10,991 --> 01:02:12,820
(Sitting down)

1938
01:02:12,821 --> 01:02:14,560
- Where have you been?
- I asked for the rice.

1939
01:02:14,561 --> 01:02:15,690
You asked for the rice?

1940
01:02:15,691 --> 01:02:16,791
(Laughing)

1941
01:02:17,391 --> 01:02:19,031
He's faster than anyone.

1942
01:02:19,161 --> 01:02:20,760
- This is his second bowl.
- Okay.

1943
01:02:20,761 --> 01:02:23,100
Your parents must be very busy.

1944
01:02:23,101 --> 01:02:24,271
You eat all so fast, right?

1945
01:02:24,941 --> 01:02:26,300
Don't you eat vegetables?

1946
01:02:26,301 --> 01:02:27,800
There are vegetables on the table.

1947
01:02:27,801 --> 01:02:29,370
They love meat so much.

1948
01:02:29,371 --> 01:02:30,851
(This is how much wrestlers can eat.)

1949
01:02:33,011 --> 01:02:36,281
(Se Yoon's team is the only table with leftover meat, due to a refill)

1950
01:02:36,381 --> 01:02:37,751
Here is the next question.

1951
01:02:37,881 --> 01:02:39,020
Guys, focus.

1952
01:02:39,021 --> 01:02:40,850
This question is also about ssireum.

1953
01:02:40,851 --> 01:02:43,520
Students cannot share the answer with the members.

1954
01:02:43,521 --> 01:02:45,090
Don't let us know the answer.

1955
01:02:45,091 --> 01:02:49,191
This is one of the signature techniques in ssireum.

1956
01:02:49,291 --> 01:02:51,901
By pulling the opponent's waist satba...

1957
01:02:52,131 --> 01:02:54,200
while pulling the leg satba downward...

1958
01:02:54,201 --> 01:02:55,331
Jong Min!

1959
01:02:56,631 --> 01:02:57,847
You don't want to hear the rest?

1960
01:02:57,871 --> 01:02:58,970
You didn't hear the rest.

1961
01:02:58,971 --> 01:03:00,541
- Go for it.
- Deulbaejigi?

1962
01:03:01,271 --> 01:03:02,541
Incorrect.

1963
01:03:02,911 --> 01:03:04,341
Oh, please!

1964
01:03:05,341 --> 01:03:07,680
By pulling the opponent's waist satba...

1965
01:03:07,681 --> 01:03:10,511
while pulling or twisting the leg satba downward...

1966
01:03:11,111 --> 01:03:12,680
(It's a technique every ssireum athlete instantly recognizes.)

1967
01:03:12,681 --> 01:03:14,651
Se Yoon!

1968
01:03:14,881 --> 01:03:16,391
- Let Seon Ho go for it.
- What?

1969
01:03:16,721 --> 01:03:18,091
- Membejigi?
- Incorrect.

1970
01:03:18,221 --> 01:03:19,990
- Flipping.
- Incorrect.

1971
01:03:19,991 --> 01:03:21,391
It's something we eat.

1972
01:03:21,421 --> 01:03:22,430
Again.

1973
01:03:22,431 --> 01:03:23,561
- Joon.
- Yes, Joon.

1974
01:03:23,791 --> 01:03:26,060
- Japchigi.
- No, again.

1975
01:03:26,061 --> 01:03:27,831
Japchigi.

1976
01:03:28,201 --> 01:03:29,201
- Japchigi?
- Yes.

1977
01:03:29,202 --> 01:03:30,231
(Sighing)

1978
01:03:30,431 --> 01:03:31,670
Incorrect.

1979
01:03:31,671 --> 01:03:33,201
(Japchigi is not the answer?)

1980
01:03:33,401 --> 01:03:35,811
(Murmuring)

1981
01:03:35,911 --> 01:03:38,341
The kids were disappointed when he said, "Japchigi."

1982
01:03:39,111 --> 01:03:40,341
Japchaegi.

1983
01:03:40,741 --> 01:03:42,011
- Come on.
- Goodness.

1984
01:03:42,351 --> 01:03:44,110
- You said it had to pull.
- DinDin.

1985
01:03:44,111 --> 01:03:45,120
It must be the answer.

1986
01:03:45,121 --> 01:03:46,280
Correct.

1987
01:03:46,281 --> 01:03:49,250
(Japchaegi is the answer.)

1988
01:03:49,251 --> 01:03:51,791
Enjoy it all you want!

1989
01:03:52,261 --> 01:03:54,691
Right, it's not japchigi. It's japchaegi.

1990
01:03:55,191 --> 01:03:57,391
That was a great move, thank you.

1991
01:03:57,761 --> 01:04:00,061
We have a refill!

1992
01:04:02,871 --> 01:04:04,270
Who wants more rice? Bring your rice.

1993
01:04:04,271 --> 01:04:05,271
(Enjoy the meat all you want!)

1994
01:04:05,272 --> 01:04:08,201
The correct term is japchaegi.

1995
01:04:08,441 --> 01:04:11,880
But sometimes it's called japchigi.

1996
01:04:11,881 --> 01:04:13,180
- What?
- So...

1997
01:04:13,181 --> 01:04:14,740
Team Joon gets extra meat too.

1998
01:04:14,741 --> 01:04:17,550
(Team Joon gets a meat refill too.)

1999
01:04:17,551 --> 01:04:19,321
This is it.

2000
01:04:19,451 --> 01:04:20,480
- Great.
- This is it.

2001
01:04:20,481 --> 01:04:21,650
Nakdong River.

2002
