01:29:37,699 --> 01:29:40,309
Let's go to the base camp now.

2755
01:29:40,639 --> 01:29:41,669
Good.

2756
01:29:42,979 --> 01:29:43,979
(Heading to the base camp)

2757
01:29:43,980 --> 01:29:46,108
- How long does it take?
- It takes five minutes.

2758
01:29:46,109 --> 01:29:47,585
(It takes 5 minutes to the base camp.)

2759
01:29:47,609 --> 01:29:49,478
- Can you make a guess?
- About what?

2760
01:29:49,479 --> 01:29:52,748
Only two of you will sleep indoors.

2761
01:29:52,749 --> 01:29:53,749
That's right.

2762
01:29:53,949 --> 01:29:55,649
The chances are 40 percent.

2763
01:29:56,489 --> 01:29:58,788
Still, it's good that two of us can sleep indoors.

2764
01:29:58,789 --> 01:29:59,828
(They're grateful that two will sleep indoors.)

2765
01:29:59,829 --> 01:30:00,858
All right.

2766
01:30:00,859 --> 01:30:01,959
Good. Let's do this.

2767
01:30:03,359 --> 01:30:05,629
It's been a while since I slept indoors last time.

2768
01:30:05,959 --> 01:30:07,569
- Really?
- Yes.

2769
01:30:08,499 --> 01:30:10,515
(Lately, whenever he played Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors, )

2770
01:30:10,539 --> 01:30:13,368
(he always got to sleep outdoors.)

2771
01:30:13,369 --> 01:30:16,339
(Outdoors)

2772
01:30:16,839 --> 01:30:18,838
- I even slept alone the other day.
- Right.

2773
01:30:18,839 --> 01:30:20,909
(He even slept outdoors alone the other day.)

2774
01:30:22,109 --> 01:30:25,178
(Thinking about that day, )

2775
01:30:25,179 --> 01:30:27,849
(he's strengthening his resolve.)

2776
01:30:28,949 --> 01:30:30,689
- We're here.
- Are we here?

2777
01:30:31,219 --> 01:30:34,758
(They've arrived at the base camp.)

2778
01:30:34,759 --> 01:30:36,089
It's a mudflat.

2779
01:30:36,299 --> 01:30:37,998
The base camp is right in front of the beach.

2780
01:30:37,999 --> 01:30:40,468
(Today's base camp is located...)

2781
01:30:40,469 --> 01:30:42,428
(right in front of the beach.)

2782
01:30:42,429 --> 01:30:43,839
Obviously, we'll be sleeping there.

2783
01:30:44,399 --> 01:30:46,339
Let's go, guys.

2784
01:30:46,539 --> 01:30:47,938
- It's here.
- It's here.

2785
01:30:47,939 --> 01:30:51,909
(Entering the base camp)

2786
01:30:52,909 --> 01:30:56,219
(Meanwhile, the sun has set.)

2787
01:30:56,779 --> 01:30:59,178
- Are you starting to feel hungry?
- Yes.

2788
01:30:59,179 --> 01:31:00,489
I'm very hungry now.

2789
01:31:00,589 --> 01:31:01,888
All right, everyone.

2790
01:31:01,889 --> 01:31:04,659
Something surprising will happen today.

2791
01:31:04,789 --> 01:31:05,919
- What?
- I see.

2792
01:31:06,019 --> 01:31:07,558
I have a strange feeling.

2793
01:31:07,559 --> 01:31:08,928
- Something surprising?
- All right.

2794
01:31:08,929 --> 01:31:10,758
Tonight's Dinner Game is...

2795
01:31:10,759 --> 01:31:12,629
I'm Sure She's My Mom.

2796
01:31:13,229 --> 01:31:14,899
- What?
- That's the game.

2797
01:31:15,369 --> 01:31:18,838
The mother of someone who will spend tonight with us...

2798
01:31:18,839 --> 01:31:20,339
is waiting behind us.

2799
01:31:20,939 --> 01:31:22,408
- Where?
- It can't be my mom.

2800
01:31:22,409 --> 01:31:24,178
- Ms. Pan Lye?
- Ms. Pan Lye?

2801
01:31:24,179 --> 01:31:25,538
- Ms. Pan Lye?
- Ms. Pan Lye?

2802
01:31:25,539 --> 01:31:27,009
Isn't it Seon Ho's mom?

2803
01:31:27,149 --> 01:31:28,348
We're in Incheon.

2804
01:31:28,349 --> 01:31:30,919
- Right. It must be Seon Ho's mom.
- That's right.

2805
01:31:31,219 --> 01:31:32,918
It could be Se Yoon's mom.

2806
01:31:32,919 --> 01:31:34,789
- Or Jong Min's mom.
- Of course.

2807
01:31:35,049 --> 01:31:36,658
Jong Min's mom...

2808
01:31:36,659 --> 01:31:38,418
- is not a good cook.
- She can't cook.

2809
01:31:38,419 --> 01:31:39,689
My mom can cook well!

2810
01:31:40,259 --> 01:31:41,688
Your mom is worse!

2811
01:31:41,689 --> 01:31:43,798
- Why is my mom bad?
- My mom can make kimchi.

2812
01:31:43,799 --> 01:31:45,598
My mom is known for her cooking.

2813
01:31:45,599 --> 01:31:48,229
Your mom's kimchi was shocking.

2814
01:31:48,729 --> 01:31:50,399
(It was 4 years ago.)

2815
01:31:50,599 --> 01:31:52,869
(A mission to find their mom's kimchi)

2816
01:31:53,669 --> 01:31:57,339
(They harshly criticized...)

2817
01:31:58,679 --> 01:32:01,279
(each other's mom's kimchi.)

2818
01:32:01,379 --> 01:32:03,949
If one of them shows up, they'll get their hair pulled.

2819
01:32:04,179 --> 01:32:05,478
"How dare you?"

2820
01:32:05,479 --> 01:32:06,718
It should be Seon Ho's mom.

2821
01:32:06,719 --> 01:32:08,848
It's someone's mother. Let's call her now.

2822
01:32:08,849 --> 01:32:10,818
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

2823
01:32:10,819 --> 01:32:12,689
- Mom!
- Mother!

2824
01:32:13,929 --> 01:32:15,788
(They see the silhouette of the mother.)

2825
01:32:15,789 --> 01:32:17,128
- Seriously?
- What?

2826
01:32:17,129 --> 01:32:19,328
(Who is she?)

2827
01:32:19,329 --> 01:32:20,399
For real?

2828
01:32:21,299 --> 01:32:22,399
What?

2829
01:32:22,699 --> 01:32:24,068
(The reason DinDin is surprised!)

2830
01:32:24,069 --> 01:32:25,768
- What are you doing here?
- Hello!

2831
01:32:25,769 --> 01:32:27,038
(DinDin's mom is here!)

2832
01:32:27,039 --> 01:32:28,039
What?

2833
01:32:28,309 --> 01:32:30,139
(Next episode)

2834
01:32:30,639 --> 01:32:33,649
(For the sons and production crew who are working hard, )

2835
01:32:34,209 --> 01:32:37,419
(DinDin's mom prepared a sumptuous feast.)

2836
01:32:37,879 --> 01:32:39,348
(A long-awaited greeting...)

2837
01:32:39,349 --> 01:32:40,588
(with the sons)

2838
01:32:40,589 --> 01:32:42,219
(But it doesn't last long.)

2839
01:32:42,619 --> 01:32:44,619
(An elegant and yet brutal truth-teller shows up.)

2840
01:32:45,659 --> 01:32:47,489
(Truth bombs to her own son)

2841
01:32:47,759 --> 01:32:50,459
(Even the eldest member can't avoid the truth bombs.)

2842
01:32:50,799 --> 01:32:53,029
(And there's the mom's true match.)

2843
01:32:53,499 --> 01:32:55,769
(DinDin's mom versus Director Joo)

2844
01:32:56,269 --> 01:32:58,168
(To feed the sons, )

2845
01:32:58,169 --> 01:32:59,169
(Wriggling)

2846
01:32:59,639 --> 01:33:02,309
(DinDin's mom struggles.)

2847
01:33:02,609 --> 01:33:05,709
(But she's just like DinDin.)

2848
01:33:06,209 --> 01:33:08,809
(I'm just trying to feed them more food.)

2849
01:33:09,179 --> 01:33:13,249
(The members and the mom work together to have dinner.)

2850
01:33:13,589 --> 01:33:16,519
(Will the members be able to enjoy the mom's cooking?)

2851
01:33:16,589 --> 01:33:18,419
Seriously, you should pay me for the meal.

2852
01:33:18,489 --> 01:33:20,258
My gosh. Seriously...

2853
01:33:20,259 --> 01:33:21,529
(See you next week.)
